  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Sport is set in its own grounds, about half way between Klosters Platz and Dorf - with easy access to the Gotschna/Parsenn and Madrisa ski areas via the regular free bus which stops right outside the hotel. </p>
<h2><span>Modern alpine style </span></h2>
<p><span>Having undergone recent refurbishments, the refreshed interiors still have that cosy alpine feel that we love when we're on a ski holiday. The modern pool area is a great place to head for a swim after a day of skiing or boarding - plus there's a sauna (adult only) to soothe any aching muscles. Many of the rooms have been updated too, so you'll have a choice between the more traditional or modern ones - they're all spacious and comfortable. With half-board included you'll have breakfast and dinner in the Panorama Room where you can enjoy lovely views over Klosters and Prättigau beyond. </span></p>
<h2>Family friendly</h2>
<p>There are loads of spots facilities available, including large indoor swimming pool, bowling alley and sports hall with table tennis - plenty to keep the children, teenagers and even grown-ups entertained when you're not out exploring the Swiss Alps. The spacious Family Rooms are perfect for a ski holiday with the kids - they have separate bedrooms and a private bathroom. </p>
<h2>Active holiday</h2>
<p><span>This is a brilliant base to access the mountains, if you're skiing or snowboarding you'll have access to the 6 ski areas under you whole area lift pass. The hotel provides a <span class="jLQSJ">guest </span><span class="jLQSJ">card</span> at check in, which also gives you free use of the train to <a data-udi="umb://document/a95de5322c984f85bcf0f013c457e8df" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a95de5322c984f85bcf0f013c457e8df}" title="Davos">Davos</a><a data-udi="umb://document/b23ef1df250240c5a3657f721fdb96d0" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/switzerland/graubunden-ski-region/klosters" title="Klosters"></a> and the resort buses to Klosters and other ski areas - so it couldn't be easier to get around whether you're skiing or not. </span></p>]]></description>
